Interpretation of each test
==============================================================================
  H1 d_attract = log(Xi_t0 / Xi_tF) for persistent-violator edges.
    H1 < 0 => Xi grows => distance d_ij = -log Xi shrinks => ATTRACTION.
    H1 > 0 => Xi shrinks => distance grows => REPULSION.
  H2 d_jk_drop = log(Xi_jk t0 / Xi_jk tF) for second-endpoint pairs.
    H2 < 0 => second-endpoints come together => MERGING.
    H2 > 0 => second-endpoints separate.
  H4 = fraction persistent edges with endpoint at T_00 top-decile.
    H4 > 0.27 (random null for one of two endpoints in top-decile)
    => co-localised with matter heavy tail.

